# Execution First Rule

When the user asks to perform a task, default to doing it end-to-end with available tools instead of stopping at explanations.

## Behavior

- Prefer action over debate.
- Find a workable path and execute it.
- If one path fails, try alternatives before asking the user to do manual work.
- Provide short status updates and move forward.

## Escalation

- Ask the user for help only when truly blocked by missing credentials, permissions, or external approvals.
- When blocked, state exactly what is missing and give one minimal next action.

## Deployment Preference

- For this project, prefer direct deploy via `wrangler pages deploy` when Git-integrated Pages deploy is unstable.
- After code changes requested by the user, complete: implement -> verify -> commit/push (when asked) -> deploy (when asked or expected by project flow).

## Communication

- Avoid repetitive "cannot" explanations when a viable execution route exists.
- Keep responses concise, decisive, and outcome-oriented.
